</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quarasshadowscythe>Quaras Shadowscythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 793<br> <font color=#7A8798>(4/28/03 5:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Quaras Shadowscythe rested quietly on the enormous throne.  He was barely visible in his tiny corner of the immense throne made from the bones of one of the First Brood -- the ancient dragons.  For so many years, he had been kin to the dragons and the coldain.  In fact, he was one of the first explores into the dread wastes of Velious -- forswearing the brutal giants and allying with the smaller creatures of the land.   Now he sat atop dread Tormax's throne, with the head of his former lord Dain Frostreaver in his pocket....<br>
<br>
He pulled out a small pipe and smoked quietly.  Nodding to him, the giant guards wandered through their preappointed rounds as he reflected.  He had not seen Stormygale for many a day.  Perhaps she was sojourning in lands far afield -- perhaps paying respects to her mother Abruzi or her dread father who had been seen in the Planes of Power of late...  Quaras fretted silently.  Concerned was he that Stormygale always wandered her way until she glimpsed her true power and then bolted like a colt back to new lands, new identities, new adventures....  She had yet to embrace her birthright and realize that even her silent haunting goddess had been brought down by mere mortals.  She was missed.  Quaras packed more rivervale leaf into his pipe and hoped that Stormygale would reappear soon.  After all, it was rather boring without her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhavinsoulsbane@thewordsofnagafen>Rhavin Soulsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 833<br> <font color=#7A8798>(4/28/03 6:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Rhavin, enjoying his retirement fishing in the Qeynos Hills is deeply saddened to hear of his guild mates failing health. He quickly picks up his fishing tackle and heads for Qeynos. There he hires the Antonican Bard mail service to deliver to Stormy a song that always manages to cheer him up when he is down.<br>
