<br>
There was quite a bit of outraged troll downstairs. She'd seen him many times, as he lurked in the shadows. He seemed kind of nice, once you got over the fact he was a troll. He certainly had a better grasp of language then most trolls she'd ever met. She kind of liked him, and they'd spoken quite often.<br>
<br>
He'd even given her some kind of shaman brew to drink for the pain she'd been suffering with. Remarkably, it seemed to help. At least she could move about without constant agony, and for that she was grateful forever. That and the fact that she no longer had to endure the king of all hangovers every morning. Or the dreams that came with all that brandy. Lizards, indeed. She blushed as she thought of it.  Maybe a little brandy now and then would be a good thing...<br>
<br>
She also wondered if she should go down and see what was going on, but the immediate yelling had stopped so she decided to clean herself up a bit. It had been a long while since she last had a bath. <br>
<br>
Opening the door, she grabbed a passing maid who had a rather frightened look on her face, and requested a tub and lots of very hot water. The heat would also do her back good. She gathered clean clothing and soaps as the maid did as she requested. A tub was brought in and filled with near boiling water. Stormygale gave the helpers all a few plat as a tip, then closed the door and stripped, shedding clothes like a snake sheding skin, she left them where they fell. They stank.<br>
<br>
As she sunk into the bath with a groan of relief, she heard men's voices through the floor. Muffled as they were, she couldn't understand it, but she wouldn't be surprised if there were some screams sometime soon. That tended to happen when one irritated a troll.<br>
<br>
Stormygale was definately feeling better. She wondered if she should actually go out this evening. Maybe try to solo a bit. Tone some muscles and get back into the swing of things. She missed her guildmates and her isolation was only causing her to fall into depression. She definately needed to get out more. <br>
<br>
A scream echoed from downstairs, disturbing her musing. Well, she'd known it was coming. She reached for her soap and started lathering her long black hair... <p><html>
